=== RATE LIMITING ANALYSIS ===

Implementation: Upstash Redis-based sliding window (lib/rate-limit.ts)
Fallback: In-memory rate limiter (lib/api/rate-limiter.ts)
Wrapper: lib/api/with-rate-limit.ts

CRITICAL: skipOnMissing defaults to TRUE
  - If UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL/TOKEN not set, rate limiting is SILENTLY SKIPPED
  - All 852 routes using applyRateLimit become unprotected if Redis is down

Coverage:
- 852/917 routes (93%) have rate limiting calls
- 65 routes (7%) have NO rate limiting

Notable unprotected routes:
- app/api/admin/backup/route.ts — backup endpoint, no rate limit
- app/api/admin/bulk/route.ts — bulk operations, no rate limit
- app/api/auth/signup/route.ts — signup endpoint, no rate limit (abuse vector)
- app/api/documents/upload/route.ts — file upload, no rate limit (DoS vector)
- 17 cron routes — acceptable (should be protected by cron secret instead)
- 10 webhook routes — acceptable (protected by signature verification)

SEVERITY:
- HIGH: auth/signup without rate limiting enables account creation abuse
- HIGH: skipOnMissing=true means ALL rate limiting fails silently if Redis unavailable
- MEDIUM: document upload without rate limiting enables storage abuse
- LOW: admin routes without rate limiting (should be auth-protected anyway)
